.TH LU\-PAR 1 "2026-04-27" "logicutils 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lu\-par \- dependency\-aware parallel task executor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lu\-par
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lu\-par
is a DAG\-aware analogue of
.BR "xargs \-P" .
Tasks are read from standard input or
.B \-\-taskfile
as tab\-separated lines:

.RS
.nf
ID\\tDEP1,DEP2,...\\tCOMMAND
.fi
.RE

The graph is verified to be acyclic (Kahn\(cqs algorithm) and tasks are
released to a worker pool as soon as all of their predecessors have
finished. Output from each task is buffered and emitted atomically when
the task completes.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-j " N"
Worker thread count.
.TP
.B \-\-keep\-going
Continue scheduling tasks whose dependencies all succeeded even if a
sibling has failed.
.TP
.BI \-\-retry= N
Retry a failed task up to \fIN\fR times before declaring it failed.
.TP
.B \-\-progress
Emit progress diagnostics on standard error.
.TP
.B \-\-transaction[=\fIPATH\fR]
Treat the entire DAG as a transaction. Snapshot \fIPATH\fR (default
\fB.lu\-store/\fR) before scheduling and, if any task ultimately fails
(after retries), restore the directory bit\-for\-bit before exiting
non\-zero. On a fully successful run the snapshot is discarded.
.TP
.BI \-\-taskfile= PATH
Read tasks from \fIPATH\fR instead of standard input.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 if every task succeeded, 1 if at least one task failed, 2 on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lu\-deps (1),
.BR lu\-queue (1)
.SH AUTHOR
NEWSNIPER.
